/parks/tails-of-manhattan\",\"description\":\"Dog lovers in New York trust Tails of Manhattan for exceptional care. This facility features secure play environments, passionate pet care professionals, offering pet care. Their services creates a...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"New York\",\"addressRegion\":\"NY\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":10,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/the-ness\",\"name\":\"the ness\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/the-ness\",\"description\":\"Dog lovers in New York trust the ness for exceptional care. This facility features professional grooming stations, trained pet care specialists, offering pet care. Their services maintains your pet's...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"New York\",\"addressRegion\":\"NY\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}3:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$c\"}}]\nd:T55e,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I walk my dog indoors in New York City?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes. Our directory currently lists 32 indoor dog parks in New York. Use the “Indoor Dog Park” filter on this page to jump straight to climate-controlled options.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How much do indoor dog parks cost in NYC?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Expect $25–$35 drop-ins, $40–$50 weekend sessions, and $150–$250 monthly memberships. NYC indoor parks often include amenities like grooming, training classes, and event space access. Some offer building resident discounts.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do NYC indoor parks require reservations?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes—most NYC indoor parks require advance reservations due to limited space and high demand. Members typically get priority booking. Walk-ins are often available but subject to capacity.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there indoor parks in Manhattan?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, though they're less common than in outer boroughs. Manhattan indoor parks are often located in apartment buildings, converted commercial spaces, or dedicated facilities. Brooklyn and Queens tend to have more standalone indoor dog park facilities.\"}}]}4:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$d\"}}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"New York\\\"}]}\"}}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$Le\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n7:[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n8:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"New York\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"Urban-proof indoor runs\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Indoor Dog Park in New York City\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-chip-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"Verified runs\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"15+\"}],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"Indoor coverage\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"All boroughs\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"New York City’s urban density and limited apartment space make indoor dog parks an essential lifestyle requirement for pet parents across the five boroughs.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"New York City is a uniquely challenging environment for dog ownership, where extreme urban density and limited apartment square footage make indoor dog parks a vital lifestyle requirement. With over 600,000 dogs in the five boroughs, competition for safe, clean exercise space is intense, especially during humid summers and slushy winters. The local scene has responded with creative real estate solutions, from rooftop facilities in the West Village to underground \\\"play labs\\\" in Brooklyn and renovated industrial warehouses in Long Island City. These facilities provide more than just treadmill exercise; they are sophisticated hubs featuring professional K9 turf and advanced air purification systems that cycle every six minutes. While \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.nycgovparks.org\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"NYC Parks\"}],null,\" maintains traditional runs, the private sector raises the bar with climate-controlled safety and concierge services essential for navigating the city’s unpredictable elements.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"The economics of NYC’s indoor play reflect the high cost of local real estate. Monthly memberships are the standard for residents, typically ranging from $150 to $250. For those seeking one-off sessions, drop-in rates hover around $25 to $35. Sustainability and safety are primary concerns; top-tier facilities require digital verification of Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella vaccinations and a mandatory behavioral assessment. New York’s pet infrastructure is supported by internal resources like our \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/owner-resources\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"owner playbook\"}],null,\", which provides data for converting commercial spaces into thriving pet communities.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"targetId\":\"park-directory\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-check\"}],\"Browse directory\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"targetId\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-geo-alt\"}],\"Open map\"]}],\"$L12\"]}],\"$L13\"]}],\"$L14\"]}]}],\"$L15\",\"$L16\",\"$L17\",\"$L18\",\"$L19\",\"$L1a\",\"$undefined\",\"$L1b\",\"$L1c\",\"$L1d\",\"$L1e\",\"$L1f\"]}]\n9:[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-new\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-container\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-grid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-column\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h4\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-heading\",\"children\":\"IndoorDogPark\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-links\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/about\",\"children\":\"About us\"}]}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/partners\",\"children\":\"Partners\"}]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-column\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h4\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-heading\",\"children\":\"Discover\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-links\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Browse parks\"}]}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/how-it-works\",\"children\":\"How it works\"}]}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L11